<FIRST>u i AM-Bangladesh-Crash     01-15 0098</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bangladesh-Crash,0101</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report Says Two Trains Collide, Killing 70, Injuring 1,000</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two trains collided in northern
Bangladesh on Sunday, killing at least 70 people and injuring 1,000
others, news reports said.
   The trains rammed into each other at the Pubail Railway Station,
about 30 miles north of Dhaka, the United News of Bangladesh
reported.
   The injured, many in serious condition, were being taken to
hospitals in the capital, the news agency said.
   Authorities were uncertain what caused the collision, the agency
said. Top government and railway officials rushed to the site, it
said.
</TEXT>
