20 years.
   ``Basically his appeal reflects the theme of the movie, which is
the American dream, having a dream and going after it despite the
odds,'' said Darrel Campbell, writer-producer of ``The Pistol.''
   ``Ronald Wilson Reagan started out like a lot of common people
and then dreamed big dreams and became an actor and then became
president of the United States, leader of the free world. Pretty
good American dream.''
