Henson Moore have written Reagan about the project, said Associate
Producer L.E. Wallace.
   But the filmmakers may have to wait in line.
   ``The president's future plans have not been determined at this
point,'' said White House spokesman Ben Jarratt in Washington.
``There have been other movie offers. There's a lot of interest in
the president, in the entertainer.''
   Maravich, who played for New Orleans and Boston in the NBA, died
in January 1988.
